    • Method Detail

      • getAccount

        Account getAccount(java.lang.Object requestData)
        Deprecated. 
        Get the account to be used for creating quote data. The account has to be associated with the policy to rate. In many cases, the account is not relevant but it can be if the rating algorithm looks at account information. In that case, selecting the right account is important. For example, if the algorithm looks at the account jurisdiction (and not policy jurisdiction), then it is important to select an account with the right jurisdiction to rate the policy.
        Parameters:
        requestData - any data needed from the quote request to figure out which account to use.
        Returns:
        the account to be used for creating quote data

      • sendQuotingData

        java.lang.Object sendQuotingData(java.io.InputStream data)
        Deprecated. 
        Send quoting data to external system. An example of an external system would be a non-PolicyCenter database. The Quote data XML would be persisted in a table as a CLOB.
        Parameters:
        data - the InputStream containing the quote data
        Returns:
        an ID object to locate where the quote data is sent to.
